Types of Classification Problems

1 Binary Classification
Only two classe

Examples:
0 / 1
Yes / No
Fraud / Not Fraud

2 Multiclass Classification

More than two classes, but only one correct class

Example:
Digit recognition → 0–9
Sentiment → Positive / Neutral / Negative

3 .Multilabel Classification

One sample can have multiple labels

Example:
Image → beach + sunset + people

Popular Classification Algorithms


1 Logistic Regression

Use when:
Linear relationship
Baseline model
Formula idea:
Probability output → sigmoid function

Key Hyperparameters
penalty = 'l1', 'l2'
C = regularization strength
solver = 'liblinear', 'lbfgs'

from sklearn.linear_model import LogisticRegression
model = LogisticRegression(C=1.0, penalty='l2')
model.fit(X_train, y_train)

2 Decision Tree

Use when:
Data is non-linear
Need interpretability

Key Hyperparameters
max_depth
min_samples_split
min_samples_leaf
criterion = 'gini' or 'entropy'

from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
model = DecisionTreeClassifier(max_depth=5)


3.3 Random Forest

Ensemble of many decision trees.

Advantages
Reduces overfitting
High accuracy

Hyperparameters
n_estimators
max_depth
max_features
min_samples_leaf

from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier
model = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators=100)

3.4 Support Vector Machine (SVM)
Use when:
High-dimensional data
Text classification

Hyperparameters
C = regularization
kernel = 'linear', 'rbf', 'poly'
gamma = kernel coefficient

from sklearn.svm import SVC
model = SVC(kernel='rbf', C=1)

3.5 K-Nearest Neighbors (KNN)
Use when:
Small dataset
Non-parametric model

Hyperparameters
n_neighbors
metric = 'euclidean'
weights = 'uniform', 'distance'

from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
model = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5)

3.6 Naive Bayes
Best for:
Text classification
Spam detection
Types
GaussianNB
MultinomialNB
BernoulliNB

3.7 Gradient Boosting / XGBoost

Use when:
Competitions
Complex patterns

Hyperparameters
learning_rate
n_estimators
max_depth
subsample

5. Important Evaluation Metrics

Classification is not judged only by accuracy.

Accuracy
Precision
Recall
F1-score
ROC-AUC

from sklearn.metrics import classification_report
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred))

6. Hyperparameter Tuning

We don’t manually try values — we use search.

Grid Search
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
param_grid = {
    'max_depth': [3,5,10],
    'n_estimators': [50,100,200]
}
grid = GridSearchCV(RandomForestClassifier(), param_grid, cv=5)
grid.fit(X_train, y_train)


8. When to Use Which Algorithm
| Dataset Type   | Best Algorithm      |
| -------------- | ------------------- |
| Small & linear | Logistic Regression |
| Non-linear     | Decision Tree       |
| High accuracy  | Random Forest       |
| Text data      | Naive Bayes / SVM   |
| Large dataset  | XGBoost             |



